cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper deals with natural language processing and text classification, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The task of identifying clickbaits in online news media can be seen as a sub-task of information retrieval, as it involves filtering out irrelevant or misleading information.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a model using deep learning methods, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of machine learning methods for clickbait detection can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The issue of clickbait headlines and their impact on online media consumption can be seen as a societal issue related to the use of technology.
